<br>
1. Chain casting. Keep an eye on your pet's health. Time the cast of a new pet so that it completes just about the time your old pet is about 5% health. Just before the cast completes, like when casting bar is below 10% or less, type /pet get lost. You can't use a hot key while casting, as you probably know, so you have to type it. Your attack hot key will work fine to send your new pet in.<br>
<br>
2. Don't get too stuck with one kind of pet at low levels. I sorta got stuck on earth pets. Even when I could not get an earth pet for one entire spell level (research failed and I couldn't find another set of components) I still went back to earth pet when I could. The others have uses, too, some situational, some general. (I don't mean to imply that you are making my mistake, just passing along my experience.)<br>
<br>
The mage boards might be useful.<br>
