<br>
You can use air (stuns) or earth (root) to do this.  Bolt spells would probably work best for this, since they pack a lot of punch.  Nuke heavy and run like mad.  Once pet roots or stuns it, nuke more.  I use to do this in the Grey because I was bored of conventional soloing, so I thought I would try something new.  Jbbot are a plus here, hehe.<br>
<br>
Healing pets:<br>
<br>
The delay will always be a problem when healing pets.  Once you get 2 heal spells, load both of them up.  You can now chain heal by casting one spell then the other.  This works very well.  Pre-POP, some mages would load up lvl 52 heal and the lvl 60 heal (rare off ssra bosses), and solo a certain Western Waste dragon.<br>
<br>
I rarely heal my pets anymore, unless I am soloing something, but most times it will be less mana to just recast a pet.<br>
